  GENESIS MAIL READER    Version 4.0 by Mercade

  x or q            Exit from mail reading mode (and delete marked messages).
  h or H [<name>]   Print all headers. (H = unread; <name> filters a sender).
  r [<num>]         Reply to current message or reply to to message <num>.
  R [<num>]         Reply (see r) and include the message you reply to.
  m <name>          Mail a message to <name>.
  f [<num>] <name>  Forward current message or message <num> to <name>.
  F [<num>] <name>  Forward (see f) and edit outgoing message first.
  d [<range>]       Mark current message or <range> for deletion.
  u [<range>]       Unmark current message or <range> for deletion.
  * [<range>]       Mark/star current message or <range> as special message.
  u* [<range>]      Unstar current message or <range> as special message.
  e                 Erase all messages marked for deletion.
  ad [<range>]      Archive current message or <range> and mark for deletion.
  ak [<range>]      Archive current message or <range> but keep from deletion.
                    Archiving is done into ~<your dir>/mail_archive/
  s [<num>] <file>  Store current message or <num> in a file named <file>.
  rs <name>         Resend last sent message again to <name>.
  [m].              Show current message [using more].
  [m]<num>          Show message number <num> [using more].
  [m]p              Show previous message [using more].
  [m]n or <return>  Show next message [using more].
  !<command>        Escape and perform <command> while in the reader,
                    even if you are writing mail! Then you can continue.
  ? [<topic>]       Print this help message, or the message on <topic>.
                    Topics: expr header

